# Learn & Use Git

[Git](https://git-scm.com) is arguably the preferred [Version Control](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Version_control) system used by developers today.

Teaching Git is outside the scope of this presentation but I suggest the following free Git courses:

- [Try Git](https://try.github.io/)
- [Learn Git](https://www.codecademy.com/learn/learn-git)
- [Learn Git with Bitbucket Cloud](https://www.atlassian.com/git/tutorials/learn-git-with-bitbucket-cloud)

---

# Install Git

Git is provided by OS X/macOS these days but lets make sure we have the latest version installed using Homebrew:

```bash
brew install git
```

Once it's done check the version of Git installed:

```bash
$ git --version
git version 2.11.0
```

